{
  "texts": [
    "In combination with a dark matter component, e.g.",
    "a Navarro-Frenk-White profile, κ * can be provided straightforwardly, albeit not in a completely unbiased way (see below).",
    "Both flux ratio and light curve microlensing data can be used to constrain the local graininess of matter, i.e.",
    "the value of κ *, and both require simulated magnification maps.",
    "These maps are generated for given κ, γ, κ * combinations derived from some macromodel and used to extract observable quantities."
  ]
}